WEBVTT

00:05.272 --> 00:08.242
♪ ♪

00:08.242 --> 00:10.310
[wind whistling]

00:11.778 --> 00:13.747
[distant screaming]

00:13.747 --> 00:15.282
[gunfire]

00:15.282 --> 00:17.317
[glass shattering]

00:19.319 --> 00:21.354
[distant snarling]

00:22.623 --> 00:24.624
[electrical buzzing]

00:25.626 --> 00:27.661
[hissing, growling]

00:31.331 --> 00:33.066
Burn in hell, zombie nun.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.103
- [distant shouting]
- [clattering]

00:36.103 --> 00:38.339
[growling]

00:38.339 --> 00:40.507
Come on, <i>hushwa</i> breath.

00:46.513 --> 00:48.548
♪ ♪

00:50.250 --> 00:51.618
Zombie diddler.

00:53.153 --> 00:54.588
[Irene]
Grandson?

00:54.588 --> 00:57.057
- Grandson?
- Yeah?

00:57.057 --> 00:59.193
Don't you think
it's time that you

00:59.193 --> 01:02.029
maybe started
cleaning up around here?

01:02.029 --> 01:03.597
One second, Grandma.

01:03.597 --> 01:06.600
Let me slice my way
to a checkpoint real quick.

01:06.600 --> 01:09.536
Well, your relatives
are at the door.

01:09.536 --> 01:12.339
They want to take you out
for some hamburgers.

01:12.339 --> 01:14.141
[sighs] Could you...

01:14.141 --> 01:17.344
Could you just tell them
I'll catch up with them later?

01:17.344 --> 01:19.413
It's a beautiful day out there.

01:19.413 --> 01:21.448
You could just go out
on the porch

01:21.448 --> 01:23.417
and visit them for a while.

01:23.417 --> 01:24.818
- You know?
- Look, I'll...

01:24.818 --> 01:27.788
I-I'll clean up today, but...

01:27.788 --> 01:30.090
could you please, please,
please tell them

01:30.090 --> 01:33.160
I'm sick or something?

01:33.160 --> 01:35.429
- All right, <i>cvpon.</i>
- Thank you, Grandma.

01:35.429 --> 01:38.065
But you need to get out of here.
You've been in here too long.

01:38.065 --> 01:41.101
You're starting
to look <i>stehvtke.</i>

01:44.137 --> 01:45.806
[Willie Jack singing softly]

01:45.806 --> 01:49.743
I'm sorry. Cheese has a touch
of the sniffles,

01:49.743 --> 01:53.781
so I don't think he's gonna
make it out today.

01:53.781 --> 01:56.584
Oh, uh, okay.

01:56.584 --> 01:58.285
Hopefully he gets better soon.

01:58.285 --> 02:01.388
Can you, uh, tell him
we miss him?

02:01.388 --> 02:05.058
Yeah. Tell him to quit
acting like that. Fuck.

02:09.730 --> 02:11.498
- I knew it.
- For fuck's sake, man.

02:12.499 --> 02:14.634
[dialing]

02:19.306 --> 02:21.242
[line ringing]

02:21.242 --> 02:22.509
[slicing sound effects]

02:22.509 --> 02:24.445
[zombie moaning]

02:24.445 --> 02:26.580
[blade clanging]

02:26.580 --> 02:29.516
That's worse than I thought.

02:29.516 --> 02:31.151
Yeah.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.554
Come on, come on.

02:33.554 --> 02:35.623
Have fun.

02:35.623 --> 02:37.224
- Geez, it's bright.
- Yep, I got him.

02:37.224 --> 02:38.425
Let's get rolling.

02:38.425 --> 02:39.660
I still don't know
what's going on.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.562
[laughs] Don't worry about it.

02:41.562 --> 02:45.165
Just go with your uncles.
They'll take good care of you.

02:45.165 --> 02:47.167
How long you been
in that room? Whole week?

02:47.167 --> 02:48.302
I don't know. What day is it?

02:48.302 --> 02:49.770
Friday, shit.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.705
Ooh, time flies
when you're fighting zombies.

02:51.705 --> 02:53.340
- You guys want to try it?
- Uh-uh.

02:53.340 --> 02:55.542
Nah, young'n,
we fight real zombies,

02:55.542 --> 02:57.278
not fake ones on TV.

02:57.278 --> 02:59.413
What kind of zombies
do you guys fight?

02:59.413 --> 03:01.115
Ones you can't see.

03:01.115 --> 03:02.383
The guilt in your hearts?

03:02.383 --> 03:03.484
- [Big] Hey.
- [laughter]

03:03.484 --> 03:05.152
No.

03:05.152 --> 03:06.654
Society. Racists.

03:06.654 --> 03:08.289
Bad guys.

03:08.289 --> 03:09.556
- Mainstream science.
- [Big] Yeah.

03:09.556 --> 03:10.824
The Man.

03:10.824 --> 03:13.127
Then what are you guys
doing here?

03:13.127 --> 03:14.528
We're on a mission.

03:14.528 --> 03:17.064
Operation: Nephew Rescue.

03:17.064 --> 03:18.499
- [Big] Ho!
- [Bucky] Hop in.

03:18.499 --> 03:20.333
Oh.

03:21.435 --> 03:23.437
[Big]
Holy shit, you kind of stink.

03:23.437 --> 03:26.439
♪ ♪

03:32.312 --> 03:34.315
<i>♪ Well, we spent last winter ♪</i>

03:34.315 --> 03:37.051
<i>♪ Dancing at
the king's ballroom... ♪</i>

03:37.051 --> 03:40.120
[song continues indistinctly
over truck stereo]

03:45.259 --> 03:47.595
[music stops, engine shuts off]

03:47.595 --> 03:49.530
[grunts]

03:49.530 --> 03:51.264
[groans]

03:52.733 --> 03:54.768
- [chuckles]
- What are we doing out here?

03:54.768 --> 03:56.203
[Big]
Field trips.

03:56.203 --> 03:57.404
National history museum.

03:57.404 --> 03:59.440
<i>Real</i> history museum.

03:59.440 --> 04:01.809
We're gonna go in there,

04:01.809 --> 04:04.111
and we're gonna catch some fish,

04:04.111 --> 04:06.680
and you're gonna learn
to provide.

04:06.680 --> 04:09.617
And then you're gonna learn
to be a man today.

04:09.617 --> 04:12.219
Ah! [grunts, laughs]

04:12.219 --> 04:13.620
You're running point.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.123
I don't even know
what that means.

04:16.123 --> 04:18.792
It means you lead the way.

04:18.792 --> 04:21.395
[laughing]

04:21.395 --> 04:23.264
What if we don't catch any fish?

04:23.264 --> 04:26.100
I brought some
frankfurter sandwiches.

04:26.100 --> 04:28.202
- No worries.
- Skoden.

04:28.202 --> 04:29.403
- <i>♪ Frankfurter ♪</i>
- Sko.

04:29.403 --> 04:30.738
<i>♪ Frankfurter ♪</i>

04:30.738 --> 04:32.706
<i>♪ Frankfurter sandwiches. ♪</i>

04:32.706 --> 04:35.609
- [birds singing]
- [machete chopping]

04:35.609 --> 04:38.145
[Cheese]
Come on, men.

04:38.145 --> 04:40.780
There's no time to rest.

04:42.349 --> 04:46.019
If you ain't moving,
you ain't surviving.

04:51.158 --> 04:53.227
Go that way.

04:53.227 --> 04:55.296
Holy fuck. Shit.

04:55.296 --> 04:57.231
He's gonna dull my blade.

04:57.231 --> 04:59.099
[Cheese]
It's already dull.

04:59.099 --> 05:00.768
[Big] Hey, you ever put
a tent together?

05:00.768 --> 05:02.303
- [Cheese] I haven't.
- [Big] Come on.

05:02.303 --> 05:04.238
- I'll show you.
- [Brownie] Shit.

05:04.238 --> 05:07.341
[laughs] We're Indian.
We don't sleep in no tent.

05:07.341 --> 05:10.311
Might as well bring
your whole house out here.

05:10.311 --> 05:12.179
I sleep in a hammock.

05:12.179 --> 05:13.747
Yeah, under all these trees,

05:13.747 --> 05:17.717
that owl's gonna shit
on your ol' beady eyes.

05:19.786 --> 05:25.059
Well, it's a good thing I sleep
with my eyes closed, unlike you.

05:25.059 --> 05:26.627
Hey, y'all watch.

05:26.627 --> 05:29.797
He sleeps with his eyes wide
open like a damn <i>stekini.</i>

05:29.797 --> 05:32.032
It's to keep an eye on you.

05:32.032 --> 05:33.567
Oh, fuck, they're gonna fight.

05:33.567 --> 05:35.102
- Here.
- You look like a dead man.

05:35.102 --> 05:37.605
I'll show you dead man,
up your bum.

05:37.605 --> 05:38.772
Yeah, yeah, you wish.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.542
[Bucky]
Take me away.

05:41.542 --> 05:44.144
- Go ahead, then.
- Fuck you want me to do?

05:44.144 --> 05:46.280
Holy shit.

05:46.280 --> 05:47.815
Do you have instructions?

05:47.815 --> 05:49.483
Yeah, I got some instructions.

05:49.483 --> 05:50.283
Hold on. Hold on there.

05:57.090 --> 05:58.692
Look at their eyes. Huh.

05:58.692 --> 06:01.061
- Look at that.
- [Big] Quit that shit.

06:01.061 --> 06:02.463
Pay attention.

06:02.463 --> 06:04.298
Watch how I do it.

06:04.298 --> 06:06.166
Take one of these little minnows
right here like this, see?

06:06.166 --> 06:07.434
Mm-hmm.

06:07.434 --> 06:10.036
All right. Hook him right there.

06:11.071 --> 06:12.306
By the gill.

06:12.306 --> 06:13.340
And go like that.

06:13.340 --> 06:16.176
All right. Now you do it.

06:17.511 --> 06:19.079
Aren't these
supposed to be alive?

06:19.079 --> 06:20.748
[Big]
Just put it on the hook.

06:20.748 --> 06:22.315
[Cheese]
Okay.

06:24.384 --> 06:26.253
Holy shit. Give it here, then.

06:26.253 --> 06:27.488
Damn.

06:27.488 --> 06:29.623
Ah.

06:29.623 --> 06:31.425
The great outdoors.

06:31.425 --> 06:33.160
[Big]
Thought we talked
about this, Brownie.

06:33.160 --> 06:34.728
Shit.

06:34.728 --> 06:37.731
Said you wouldn't blaze up
in front of the kid, goddamn it.

06:37.731 --> 06:40.067
It's not a drug. It's medicine.

06:40.067 --> 06:42.369
That shit will
slow your brain down.

06:42.369 --> 06:44.571
That's the point.

06:45.772 --> 06:47.608
What's Bucky doing?

06:47.608 --> 06:50.578
[Brownie]
Oh, that's the old Muscogee way
of fishing.

06:50.578 --> 06:52.513
Drunk root.

06:52.513 --> 06:55.649
They grind that root down,
pound it down to a powder,

06:55.649 --> 06:58.619
then they splash it around
the water like that,

06:58.619 --> 07:00.588
and the fish are supposed
to get drunk.

07:00.588 --> 07:03.457
And then they just float up
to the surface

07:03.457 --> 07:07.628
and you grab 'em
and you put 'em in your bag!

07:07.628 --> 07:10.564
- [laughs]
- You know, that's actually
a pretty good idea.

07:10.564 --> 07:12.299
Scaring the fish away
is what he's doing!

07:12.299 --> 07:15.336
Bucky! Hey. Quit that.

07:15.336 --> 07:17.171
Holy shit, that guy.

07:17.171 --> 07:20.474
Hey, you can join me out here
if you want to, <i>cvpon.</i>

07:20.474 --> 07:22.610
You know, it just rained a lot,

07:22.610 --> 07:25.746
so there's probably
a lot of E. coli, so...

07:25.746 --> 07:27.481
No, thanks.

07:27.481 --> 07:30.183
What the fuck's E. coli?

07:33.287 --> 07:34.755
[Cheese]
So, you just...

07:34.755 --> 07:37.424
throw it out, reel it in...

07:37.424 --> 07:38.692
[chuckles]

07:38.692 --> 07:40.527
...and eat it?

07:41.495 --> 07:43.230
This is riveting.

07:43.230 --> 07:45.499
Nah, that's not what it's about.

07:45.499 --> 07:49.303
You got to change that
colonized mindset, nephew.

07:49.303 --> 07:52.038
You know,
it's not about the fish.

07:52.973 --> 07:55.609
You got to turn that
internal pressure gauge off.

07:55.609 --> 07:58.345
Got your mind going so fast.

07:58.345 --> 08:01.348
Look at that dirt on the ground.

08:01.348 --> 08:03.717
Go ahead, touch it.

08:05.752 --> 08:08.455
Pick it up.
Take a good look at it.

08:09.823 --> 08:11.591
Smell it.

08:12.626 --> 08:14.261
[sniffs]

08:16.396 --> 08:20.334
There's nothing like that
anywhere else in the world.

08:20.334 --> 08:22.236
It exists only here.

08:22.236 --> 08:25.706
And you're a big part
of that right now.

08:25.706 --> 08:28.141
Take a big breath.

08:29.509 --> 08:31.111
[inhales]

08:31.111 --> 08:34.648
That air you're taking in
is all the medicine

08:34.648 --> 08:37.351
and chemicals
from all these trees

08:37.351 --> 08:40.187
going right into your lungs.

08:40.187 --> 08:43.323
[laughs] That's healing.

08:46.526 --> 08:48.329
Now, quiet.

08:48.329 --> 08:49.729
Listen real good.

08:51.632 --> 08:53.300
[birds singing]

08:53.300 --> 08:55.135
[leaves rustling]

08:58.105 --> 08:59.606
[buzzing]

09:01.408 --> 09:03.611
[splashing]

09:03.611 --> 09:06.179
[soft rustling]

09:08.115 --> 09:10.050
- What am I listening for?
- Shh.

09:10.050 --> 09:11.752
Listen.

09:11.752 --> 09:13.754
[farts]

09:13.754 --> 09:15.456
- [laughs]
- Gross!

09:15.456 --> 09:17.191
- Disgusting.
- That's it.

09:17.191 --> 09:20.160
That's it. That's what it's
all about, see?

09:20.160 --> 09:23.464
It's about us being out here
in nature together.

09:23.464 --> 09:25.432
[Cheese]
I'm just gonna keep
my mouth covered

09:25.432 --> 09:27.334
till the smell goes away.

09:27.334 --> 09:29.336
- [Brownie chuckles]
- [Big] Oh, fuck, got bites.

09:29.336 --> 09:32.206
- [Bucky] Hey.
- [Brownie] Get it, get it.

09:32.206 --> 09:33.774
- Goddamn it.
- [Brownie] Oh.

09:33.774 --> 09:36.243
Shit, I had one.

09:36.243 --> 09:37.577
[Bucky]
Ah.

09:39.146 --> 09:40.748
[laughs]

09:40.748 --> 09:43.183
Quit fucking cheating, Bucky.

09:43.183 --> 09:44.451
Fucker.

09:45.419 --> 09:45.719
It ain't right.

09:51.758 --> 09:54.694
<i>♪ Frankfurter sandwich. ♪</i>

09:57.364 --> 09:59.433
This is the key.

09:59.433 --> 10:01.702
Get some good oil,
some Himalayan salt.

10:01.702 --> 10:03.237
Can't go wrong.

10:03.237 --> 10:05.306
I carry this stuff with me
everywhere I go.

10:05.306 --> 10:06.773
It's good medicine.

10:13.246 --> 10:15.149
So, um...

10:15.149 --> 10:17.083
What's going on with you, youngblood?

10:20.220 --> 10:23.290
I don't know, it's...

10:23.290 --> 10:25.459
My friends are older than I am,

10:25.459 --> 10:27.528
and it just feels
like the differences

10:27.528 --> 10:31.332
between me and them are just
getting bigger and bigger.

10:31.332 --> 10:34.468
Eventually, they'll find
other people and...

10:34.468 --> 10:36.470
leave me behind.

10:36.470 --> 10:38.639
Like everyone else.

10:38.639 --> 10:40.674
Guess I'm just...

10:40.674 --> 10:43.777
consciously pushing them away.

10:45.345 --> 10:47.380
I don't know.

10:48.482 --> 10:50.551
Well, you know...

10:50.551 --> 10:54.755
we're all connected
on a molecular level.

10:54.755 --> 10:59.426
So, even if you're
not seeing them,

10:59.426 --> 11:02.263
the, uh, quantum thread

11:02.263 --> 11:04.664
cannot be disentangled.

11:05.832 --> 11:07.500
What?

11:08.635 --> 11:10.137
Uh, let me put it this way.

11:10.137 --> 11:13.374
Uh, the soul contract

11:13.374 --> 11:17.510
cannot be, um, untethered.

11:18.612 --> 11:20.080
What?

11:20.080 --> 11:23.116
These are bonds
you don't want to break.

11:26.653 --> 11:28.055
Food almost ready?

11:28.055 --> 11:30.291
Almost.

11:30.291 --> 11:33.227
Uh, I'm gonna need some more
firewood, though, soon.

11:33.227 --> 11:36.363
Aho. Cheese. Sko.

11:37.464 --> 11:39.733
Holy shit, hurry up.

11:39.733 --> 11:43.604
Take you out here in the woods
and introduce you to Bigfoot.

11:43.604 --> 11:45.672
♪ ♪

11:53.280 --> 11:56.250
Got to be on the lookout
when you're out here.

11:56.250 --> 11:58.485
Bigfoot country.

11:58.485 --> 12:01.354
Get reports on him all the time.

12:02.756 --> 12:04.758
Big, do you really believe
in Bigfoot?

12:04.758 --> 12:07.595
One doesn't believe in Bigfoot.

12:07.595 --> 12:10.464
Bigfoot don't care
if you believe or not.

12:10.464 --> 12:12.466
He's out there.

12:12.466 --> 12:14.435
What if you never seen a dog?

12:14.435 --> 12:16.470
Or a rhinoceros?

12:16.470 --> 12:19.807
Somebody showed you a drawing,
said this is out there?

12:19.807 --> 12:22.075
Shit, you'd think
they was crazy.

12:23.076 --> 12:24.678
Humans are stupid.

12:24.678 --> 12:26.279
Never forget that.

12:27.047 --> 12:29.416
I guess I just wish
I could see one, you know,

12:29.416 --> 12:31.051
if they're... if they're
really out there.

12:31.051 --> 12:33.587
Hey, quit that.
Don't be calling up spirits.

12:33.587 --> 12:35.623
Sure as shit they'll show up.

12:35.623 --> 12:37.324
Spit on that ground.

12:37.324 --> 12:39.526
Spit so those thoughts leave
your head in that way.

12:39.526 --> 12:41.361
Holy Christ.

12:44.364 --> 12:47.101
I seen him. Four of 'em.

12:47.101 --> 12:48.702
- For real?
- Yeah.

12:50.170 --> 12:52.806
<i>Yeah, I was about your age.</i>

12:52.806 --> 12:55.743
<i>Just alone out in the woods
when I saw them.</i>

12:55.743 --> 12:58.112
[Cheese]
<i>Were they hairy?</i>

12:58.112 --> 13:00.514
[Big]
<i>Well, they all were kind of,
back then.</i>

13:00.514 --> 13:02.516
<i>You know, women didn't shave.</i>

13:02.516 --> 13:04.184
<i>I actually liked it better.</i>

13:04.184 --> 13:06.186
It's organtic.

13:06.186 --> 13:07.521
What?

13:07.521 --> 13:08.589
Huh?

13:08.589 --> 13:11.025
Oh, yeah, Bigfoot.

13:11.025 --> 13:13.160
Yeah, fuck.
What, do you think he shaved?

13:13.160 --> 13:15.296
[Cheese]
<i>I don't know.</i>

13:15.296 --> 13:17.398
[Big]
<i>Started with that smell.</i>

13:17.398 --> 13:18.632
[Cheese]
<i>What'd it smell like?</i>

13:18.632 --> 13:19.767
[Big]
<i>Hard to explain.</i>

13:19.767 --> 13:21.235
[sniffs]

13:21.235 --> 13:22.435
[Cheese]
<i>If you had to describe it.</i>

13:24.204 --> 13:25.506
Stink.

13:25.506 --> 13:27.307
[rustling]

13:28.442 --> 13:30.344
[Cheese]
<i>What'd it do?</i>

13:30.344 --> 13:34.315
[Big]
<i>It just kind of...
stared me a long time.</i>

13:34.315 --> 13:36.584
<i>Felt like forever.</i>

13:36.584 --> 13:38.686
Yeah, I remember I had one tear

13:38.686 --> 13:42.255
just kind of fall down
my cheek real slow-like.

13:43.690 --> 13:45.092
[Cheese]
<i>Then what happened?</i>

13:45.092 --> 13:47.094
Shh. Christ.

13:47.094 --> 13:48.729
I'm sorry, it's just...

13:48.729 --> 13:51.298
You're good at storytelling.
Full of suspense, you know?

13:51.298 --> 13:53.601
I know.

13:53.601 --> 13:55.603
Then they just walked away.

13:55.603 --> 13:57.338
Oh.

13:57.338 --> 14:00.307
That's... anticlimactic.

14:00.307 --> 14:03.343
So what lesson did you get
from that, hmm?

14:04.144 --> 14:06.113
[Cheese]
Don't be a pervert in the woods?

14:06.113 --> 14:07.347
[Big]
No. Shit.

14:09.583 --> 14:12.586
Sometimes we need to cry
even though we don't know it?

14:14.788 --> 14:16.290
Yeah, that's right.

14:16.290 --> 14:18.259
Yeah, that's right, aho, aho.

14:18.259 --> 14:20.461
Also Bigfoot is real. Hmm?

14:20.461 --> 14:21.695
Says you.

14:21.695 --> 14:23.631
Shitass.

14:23.631 --> 14:26.200
- What are you even looking for?
- Kindling.

14:26.200 --> 14:27.300
Get that fire going.

14:33.540 --> 14:35.509
Ah, good greens, good greens.

14:35.509 --> 14:38.712
Oh, got the good greens
for you here.

14:38.712 --> 14:40.780
Mm, you're gonna love it.

14:41.548 --> 14:46.287
And I got a homemade
hot sauce here

14:46.287 --> 14:49.223
that you need to just sprinkle.

14:49.223 --> 14:50.824
One dab will do ya.

14:50.824 --> 14:52.592
Let me have that.

14:54.394 --> 14:56.730
Oh, <i>mvto, mvto.</i>

14:56.730 --> 14:58.499
You know, fish just don't
taste the same

14:58.499 --> 15:00.534
after I busted
those fish fuckers.

15:00.534 --> 15:03.137
- [laughs]
- Yeah, you got to
drench it in hot sauce.

15:03.137 --> 15:04.605
[Bucky]
I'm warning you.

15:04.605 --> 15:07.074
Ah, shit, I eat hot coals.

15:07.074 --> 15:08.742
I eat ghost peppers like candy.

15:08.742 --> 15:10.511
There we go.

15:10.511 --> 15:12.146
Ho.

15:12.146 --> 15:13.547
[grunts]

15:13.547 --> 15:15.248
Bon appétit.

15:16.216 --> 15:17.517
Mm.

15:18.752 --> 15:22.522
Mm. Good.

15:26.126 --> 15:28.228
[rumbling]

15:29.496 --> 15:30.664
[coughing]

15:30.664 --> 15:32.733
- Holy fuck, Bucky.
- [laughter]

15:32.733 --> 15:35.269
Jesus Christ,
what was in that shit?

15:35.269 --> 15:36.670
I told you.

15:36.670 --> 15:40.474
It's my own mix of ghost peppers
and jalapeños.

15:40.474 --> 15:43.143
But, uh, you know,
the type doesn't matter.

15:43.143 --> 15:46.413
It's how you grow it.
But, and when I tell you

15:46.413 --> 15:49.116
that one dab will do you...

15:49.116 --> 15:50.417
[laughter]

15:50.417 --> 15:52.720
I'll fucking arrest
your goddamn ass.

15:52.720 --> 15:55.422
<i>♪ Life was filled
with guns and war ♪</i>

15:55.422 --> 16:00.227
<i>♪ And everyone got trampled
on the floor ♪</i>

16:00.227 --> 16:01.762
♪ ♪

16:01.762 --> 16:06.467
<i>♪ I wish we'd all been ready ♪</i>

16:06.467 --> 16:10.237
<i>♪ Children died,
the days grew cold ♪</i>

16:10.237 --> 16:14.441
<i>♪ A piece of bread
could buy a bag of gold... ♪</i>

16:14.441 --> 16:16.510
[all sighing]

16:16.510 --> 16:19.380
<i>♪ I wish we'd all
been ready... ♪</i>

16:19.380 --> 16:21.081
You ever sword-fight?

16:21.081 --> 16:22.749
Hey, quit that. Shit.

16:23.750 --> 16:26.153
Ugh. [sighs]

16:26.153 --> 16:28.655
[birds singing]

16:34.194 --> 16:36.596
So, what now?

16:37.598 --> 16:39.600
This.

16:39.600 --> 16:41.702
- This?
- [Big] Yeah.

16:41.702 --> 16:44.338
This is what we do in the woods.

16:44.338 --> 16:46.373
You're just not used to it.

16:46.373 --> 16:49.109
You guys don't play charades
or guessing games?

16:53.614 --> 16:55.149
[sighs]

16:55.149 --> 16:56.750
- [Cheese] I have an idea.
- Huh?

16:56.750 --> 16:58.218
Why don't we do something
that I learned

16:58.218 --> 16:59.420
when I was at the boys' home?

16:59.420 --> 17:01.689
So, we'd get a stick...

17:01.689 --> 17:03.757
- Yeah?
- Person who has the stick

17:03.757 --> 17:06.193
would talk,
and then we'd pass it around.

17:06.193 --> 17:07.761
I'll go first.

17:07.761 --> 17:09.363
My name's Cheese.

17:09.363 --> 17:12.132
My pronouns are he, him and his.

17:12.132 --> 17:13.434
Ah, shit.

17:13.434 --> 17:15.035
And...

17:15.035 --> 17:17.470
I think I'm
a pretty happy person.

17:19.072 --> 17:21.174
Generally speaking.

17:23.243 --> 17:25.546
Um...

17:25.546 --> 17:27.414
[chuckles]

17:27.414 --> 17:29.416
I'm Brownie.

17:33.453 --> 17:35.055
I'm a sex addict.

17:35.055 --> 17:36.257
- [exclaims] Fuck.
- [laughter]

17:36.257 --> 17:37.658
[Brownie]
And, um...

17:37.658 --> 17:39.426
[laughter]

17:39.426 --> 17:41.328
And...

17:41.328 --> 17:45.165
uh, I guess I'm glad to be here.

17:45.165 --> 17:47.668
[laughter]

17:47.668 --> 17:51.472
Hello. This thing working?

17:51.472 --> 17:53.140
[chuckling]

17:53.140 --> 17:56.710
Ah, well, I'm... I'm Bucky.

17:56.710 --> 18:01.181
And, uh, my pronouns
are the same as Cheese's.

18:01.181 --> 18:02.549
[Big grunts]

18:02.549 --> 18:05.552
- I'm just happy to be here.
- [Big] Aho.

18:05.552 --> 18:08.122
Well, see?
We're getting somewhere.

18:08.122 --> 18:09.556
[Big]
Ah.

18:09.556 --> 18:12.326
[Cheese]
How about you, Big?
How you feeling?

18:12.326 --> 18:13.694
What do you mean?

18:13.694 --> 18:16.196
Your emotions. How you feeling?

18:22.569 --> 18:24.104
[sighs]

18:25.138 --> 18:27.207
Well...

18:27.207 --> 18:29.109
I'm Big and...

18:29.109 --> 18:32.513
oh, I don't know, shit.

18:32.513 --> 18:35.583
Well, I guess I realized
that I've...

18:35.583 --> 18:37.617
been bottling up a lot of pain.

18:40.354 --> 18:42.289
You know, as men,
you know, we're...

18:42.289 --> 18:44.525
taught not to recognize
those feelings and...

18:44.525 --> 18:46.594
[Big clears throat]

18:46.594 --> 18:48.428
And, um...

18:49.796 --> 18:52.032
Lost a friend.

18:55.469 --> 18:57.437
Two of 'em.

18:59.506 --> 19:03.109
Ah, I put that all on myself.

19:04.177 --> 19:06.413
But I knew in my heart,
you know?

19:06.413 --> 19:09.583
I was... I was trying to help.

19:09.583 --> 19:12.652
I was trying to be a...
a good man.

19:15.489 --> 19:17.591
You know what?

19:17.591 --> 19:20.060
I was just...

19:20.060 --> 19:22.195
avoiding it, you know?

19:23.263 --> 19:24.565
And that guilt.

19:24.565 --> 19:27.100
Fuck, it started
eating me up in that way.

19:30.070 --> 19:34.208
I realized that we all
make mistakes. [sniffles]

19:34.208 --> 19:36.643
And it's okay.

19:38.412 --> 19:40.113
[sobbing]

19:41.381 --> 19:42.483
Let it out.

19:42.483 --> 19:44.484
- [crying]
- All right.

19:45.485 --> 19:46.687
Just let it all out.

19:46.687 --> 19:48.755
[crying continues]

19:52.259 --> 19:53.560
[Bucky]
Okay.

20:01.535 --> 20:04.405
W-We had a friend that we lost.

20:04.405 --> 20:06.740
- He died?
- No.

20:06.740 --> 20:08.442
We just lost him.

20:08.442 --> 20:10.544
He...

20:13.614 --> 20:16.817
I-I don't think he knew
that he could...

20:16.817 --> 20:19.185
rely on us.

20:20.354 --> 20:21.655
He...

20:22.856 --> 20:24.324
Yeah.

20:25.559 --> 20:27.727
He-he had nobody.

20:40.607 --> 20:42.576
Uh... [clears throat]

20:42.576 --> 20:44.411
And, uh...

20:44.411 --> 20:46.346
[clears throat]

20:47.714 --> 20:50.383
You remind us of that friend.

20:54.421 --> 20:56.790
His name was Maximus.

20:59.393 --> 21:02.663
And your grandma...

21:02.663 --> 21:07.501
she saw you were pulling away,
you know, like him.

21:07.501 --> 21:09.370
And...

21:09.370 --> 21:13.374
something happened, you know?

21:13.374 --> 21:16.410
- We didn't believe him.
- [Big sniffles]

21:16.410 --> 21:20.146
He needed us, and, um...

21:21.815 --> 21:24.150
We turned our back on him.

21:25.218 --> 21:27.755
I mean, there was...

21:27.755 --> 21:29.690
no way you could've known.

21:29.690 --> 21:31.258
[Bucky]
I should've.

21:32.292 --> 21:34.295
I should've known 'cause...

21:34.295 --> 21:36.130
Well, we're just men, you know?

21:36.130 --> 21:38.032
We don't know everything.

21:38.032 --> 21:40.634
- We make mistakes and...
- [Big sobbing]

21:40.634 --> 21:42.803
We don't know shit!

21:42.803 --> 21:45.105
[sobbing]

21:45.105 --> 21:48.108
[Big, Bucky and Brownie sobbing]

21:55.082 --> 21:57.051
[Cheese]
You know...

21:57.051 --> 22:01.388
this was more effective
than I thought.

22:02.756 --> 22:05.192
I don't know Maximus,

22:05.192 --> 22:07.294
but I promise I won't
turn out like him.

22:07.294 --> 22:08.362
[Big]
Okay.

22:08.362 --> 22:10.598
I have you guys.

22:10.598 --> 22:13.634
I have my grandma.

22:13.634 --> 22:15.202
My friends.

22:15.202 --> 22:16.804
[Bucky]
Yeah.

22:16.804 --> 22:18.605
And I'll, uh...

22:19.773 --> 22:22.242
...see them as much as I can.

22:24.544 --> 22:28.181
Yeah. That's good. Yeah.

22:34.154 --> 22:35.689
[blowing nose]

22:36.690 --> 22:38.626
[Big]
Aho, shit.

22:38.626 --> 22:41.629
Let's go watch that sunset, huh?

22:41.629 --> 22:43.130
About to get dark.

22:43.130 --> 22:44.998
[sniffles]

22:45.799 --> 22:47.468
- [Brownie] Yeah.
- Oh!

22:47.468 --> 22:49.636
I have to make
a phone call first.

22:52.105 --> 22:56.143
Yeah, thank you all for bringing
out this bounty, youngbloods.

22:56.143 --> 22:57.777
- Aho.
- Aho.
- Aho.

22:59.279 --> 23:02.149
Now we're living off
the fat of the land.

23:02.149 --> 23:03.817
[light laughter]

23:03.817 --> 23:09.757
<i>♪ Love me now I am home ♪</i>

23:09.757 --> 23:11.692
♪ ♪

23:11.692 --> 23:17.765
<i>♪ Ignore the days
I left you here alone ♪</i>

23:17.765 --> 23:20.100
♪ ♪

23:20.100 --> 23:23.169
<i>♪ Dream of some-- ♪</i>

23:28.675 --> 23:30.510
[grunting]

23:32.245 --> 23:38.218
<i>♪ Hours hold up your dream now ♪</i>

23:38.218 --> 23:41.622
<i>♪ What we need. ♪</i>

23:41.622 --> 23:43.690
♪ ♪

